I am a second year Ph.D student in Computer Science at Stanford University, co-advised by Prof. Peter Bailis and Prof. Philip Levis. I am a member of the Stanford Future Data Systems group, and the Secure Internet of Things Project. I am broadly interested in efficient and effective data analytics for the Internet of Things sensor data. My current research focuses on human-friendly time series visualization.
I graduated from California Institute of Technology in 2015 with a B.S. in Computer Science. Before that, I attended Nanjing Foreign Language School in Nanjing, China.
